-fleitz-john-bolton-national-security-council/index.html|title=John Bolton's chief of staff out at National Security Council|accessdate=November 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113024923/https://www.cnn.com/2018/10/15/politics/fred-fleitz-john-bolton-national-security-council/index.html|archive-date=November 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| <br>[[Joan Virginia O\u2019Hara]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[United States National Security Council|Executive Secretary of the National Security Council]]\n| November 19, 2018\n| October 11, 2019\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/10/11/national-security-council-staff-changes-044622|title=JTrump's new national security adviser shakes up staff|accessdate=October 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011232208/https://www.politico.com/news/2019/10/11/national-security-council-staff-changes-044622|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Rich Higgins (official)|Rich Higgins]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Director of Strategic Planning of the National Security Council\n| January 20, 2017\n| July 21, 2017\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/08/a-national-security-council-staffer-is-forced-out-over-a-controversial-memo/535725/|title=An NSC Staffer Is Forced Out Over a Controversial Memo|accessdate=November 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170814175209/https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/08/a-national-security-council-staffer-is-forced-out-over-a-controversial-memo/535725/|archive-date=August 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tera Dahl]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Deputy Chief of Staff for the National Security Council\n| January 20, 2017\n| July 6, 2017\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/07/06/politics/tera-dahl-bannon-ally-national-security-council/index.html|title=Bannon ally leaves the National Secu