a probe moves to senior ODNI post|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Earl Matthews]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Senior Director for Defense Policy and Strategy of the National Security Council\n| July 14, 2018\n| November 7, 2019\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/07/earl-matthews-nsc-ukraine-067363|title=NSC official who attended key Ukraine meetings to leave post|accessdate=November 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107195833/https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/07/earl-matthews-nsc-ukraine-067363|archive-date=November 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:William Happer by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg|100px]]<br>[[William Happer]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Senior Director for Emerging Technologies of the National Security Council\n| September 2018\n| September 11, 2019\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/11/climate/william-happer-climate-change-white-house.html|title=Climate Denialist to Depart White House National Security Council|accessdate=September 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915181012/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/11/climate/william-happer-climate-change-white-house.html|archive-date=September 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Luciana_Borio_official_portrait.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Luciana Borio]]\n| style=\"background:lightgrey\"| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Director for Medical and Biodefense Preparedness Policy of the National Security Council\n| July 2017\n| May 2018\n| \n|-\n| [[Rob Porter]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[White House Office of the Staff Secretary|White House Staff Secretary]]\n| January 20, 2017\n| February 7, 2018\n| Resigned his position as White House Staff Secretary after [[domestic abuse]] allegations from both of his former wives came to public attention<ref>{{cite news|last1=Prokopandrew|first1=Andrew|title=Rob Porter's domestic violence scandal, and wh