es up|last1=Westwood|first1=Sarah|last2=Brown|first2=Pamela|date=May 21, 2019|publisher=CNN|access-date=May 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522211042/https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/21/politics/shahira-knight-white-house-exit/index.html|archive-date=May 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75px]]<br>Special Assistant to the President (Economic Policy)\n| January 20, 2017\n| July 2018 \n|\n|-\n| [[Mary Elizabeth Taylor]] \n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75px]]<br>White House Deputy Director of Legislative Affairs of Nominations\n| January 2017\n| October 2018\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Gary Cohn at Regional Media Day (cropped).png|100px]]<br>[[Gary Cohn (investment banker)|Gary Cohn]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[United States National Economic Council|Director of the National Economic Council]]\n| January 20, 2017\n| March 13, 2018\n| Announcement followed [[Trump tariffs|Trump's proposal]] to impose import tariffs on steel and aluminum, and Trump's cancellation of a meeting with end-users of steel and aluminium that Cohn had arranged in an attempt to dissuade the president from the planned tariffs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/03/06/gary-cohn-plans-to-resign-as-trumps-top-economic-advisor-new-york-times.html|title=Gary Cohn resigns as Trump's top economic advisor|last1=Mangan|first1=Dan|last2=Pramuk|first2=Jacob|date=March 6, 2018|work=CNBC|accessdate=March 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306224720/https://www.cnbc.com/2018/03/06/gary-cohn-plans-to-resign-as-trumps-top-economic-advisor-new-york-times.html|archive-date=March 6, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Jeremy Katz]]\n| [[File:US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg|75x75px]]<br>Deputy Director of the National Economic Council for Economic Policy<br>(Domestic Policy)\n| January 22, 2017\n| January 2018\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/366221-white-house-economic-adviser-jeremy-katz-leaving-i