hy-Under Secretary of the Army.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Ryan McCarthy (U.S. Army)|Ryan McCarthy]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"| August 3, 2017\n| style=\"background:gold\"| November 20, 2017\n|\n|-\n| style=\"background:gold\"| June 23, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\"| July 15, 2019\n| McCarthy was Acting Army Secretary while Esper was Acting Defense Secretary. When Esper was confirmed as Defense Secretary, McCarthy became Acting Army Secretary yet again. On September 26, 2019, the Senate confirmed McCarthy as Army Secretary.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[File:Mark T. Esper.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Mark Esper]]\n| November 20, 2017\n| July 23, 2019\n| Became the [[United States Secretary of Defense]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[File:United States Department of Defense Seal.svg|70px]]<br>Secretary of Defense\n| style=\"background:gold\"| June 23, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\"| July 15, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Pres. Trump appointed Esper Acting Defense Secretary and nominated him for Defense Secretary. By law, Esper could not serve as Acting Secretary during the confirmation process, so Spencer was Acting Defense Secretary for a brief period.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[File:Richard V. Spencer.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Richard V. Spencer|Richard Spencer]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"| July 15, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\"| July 23, 2019\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[File:Seal of the United States Department of the Navy.svg|70px]]<br>[[United States Secretary of the Navy|Secretary of the Navy]]\n| August 3, 2017\n| November 24, 2019\n| Forced out after clashing with Pres. Trump over disciplining Navy SEAL [[Eddie Gallagher (Navy SEAL)|Eddie Gallagher]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EKLLjE8W4AA_rgo.jpg|title=Richard Spencer termination letter|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=November 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125001322/https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EKLLjE8W4AA_rgo.jpg|archive-date=November 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.co