abe stepping down |date=January 29, 2018 |accessdate=January 29, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129174634/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/fbi-deputy-director-andrew-mccabe-stepping-down-n842176 |archive-date=January 29, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On March 16, 2018, Jeff Sessions fired McCabe 26 hours before his scheduled retirement.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|last1=Zapotosky|first1=Matt|title=FBI's Andrew McCabe is fired a little more than 24 hours before he could retire|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/fbis-andrew-mccabe-is-fired-a-little-more-than-24-hours-before-he-could-retire/2018/03/16/e055a22a-2895-11e8-bc72-077aa4dab9ef_story.html|website=The Washington Post|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=March 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317020927/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/fbis-andrew-mccabe-is-fired-a-little-more-than-24-hours-before-he-could-retire/2018/03/16/e055a22a-2895-11e8-bc72-077aa4dab9ef_story.html|archive-date=March 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/3/16/17121196/andrew-mccabe-fired-sessions-trump-fbi|title=Andrew McCabe, the former FBI deputy director targeted by Trump, was just fired|work=Vox|access-date=March 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317074525/https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/3/16/17121196/andrew-mccabe-fired-sessions-trump-fbi|archive-date=March 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Sessions said he based his action on reports from the DOJ Inspector General and the FBI's disciplinary office saying that McCabe had made unauthorized releases of information to the media and had \"lacked candor\" in talking about it. McCabe denied he had ever been dishonest and charged that his firing was politically motivated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/378826-sessions-fires-mccabe-from-fbi|title=Sessions 