59-11e8-8acf-ad2991367d9d_story.html |title= Trumps Drug Policy Deputy Chief of Staff to Step Down |accessdate= April 25, 2018 |author= Robert O\u2019Harrow or the Washington Post |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180414071657/https://www.washingtonpost.com/amphtml/investigations/trumps-24-year-old-drug-policy-appointee-to-step-down-by-months-end/2018/01/24/77ce5656-0159-11e8-8acf-ad2991367d9d_story.html |archive-date= April 14, 2018 |url-status= live }}</ref> Hired by [[United States Department of Housing and Urban Development|HUD]] in March 2018 on [[opioid]] policy, he said in January he was \"unfairly criticized\".<ref>Weiner, Mark, [http://www.syracuse.com/politics/index.ssf/2018/03/skaneateles_grad_lands_new_job_in_trump_administration_after_resigning_drug_post.html \"Skaneateles grad lands new job in Trump Administration after resigning drug post\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515044033/http://www.syracuse.com/politics/index.ssf/2018/03/skaneateles_grad_lands_new_job_in_trump_administration_after_resigning_drug_post.html |date=May 15, 2018 }}, syracuse.com, March 9, 2018. Retrieved May 14, 2018.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Maria Pagan]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[File:US-EOP-OfficeOfAdministration-Seal.svg|75x75px]]\n[[Office of the United States Trade Representative|Trade Representative]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"|January 20, 2017 \n| style=\"background:gold\"|March 2, 2017\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Stephen P. Vaughn.png|100px]]<br>[[Stephen Vaughn]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"|March 2, 2017\n| style=\"background:gold\"|May 15, 2017\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Kevin Hassett official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Kevin Hassett]]\n| [[File:Council of Economic Advisers.png|75x75px]]<br>Chairman of the [[Council of Economic Advisers]]\n| September 13, 2017\n| July 15, 2019\n| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/kevin-hassett-top-white-house-economic-adviser-leaving-trump-says-n1012996|title=Kevin Hassett, top White House economic adviser, is leaving,