es-post-1342090|title=Another top immigration official to leave Friday|publisher=Politico|date=April 10, 2019|first=Ted|last=Hesson|access-date=April 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410210717/https://www.politico.com/story/2019/04/10/ronald-vitiello-ice-leaves-post-1342090|archive-date=April 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[File:U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) Logo.svg|200px]]<br>[[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement|Director of U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement]]\n| style=\"background:gold\" | June 30, 2018\n| style=\"background:gold\" | April 12, 2019\n|-\n| [[File:Matthew Albence official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Matthew Albence]]\n| style=\"background:gold\" | April 13, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\" | May 28, 2019\n| \n|-\n| [[File:ICE Director Mark Morgan.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Mark Morgan (law enforcement officer)|Mark Morgan]]\n| style=\"background:gold\" | May 28, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\" | July 7, 2019\n| Named Acting Commissioner of CBP. Deputy Director Albence becomes Acting Director once again. The Trump administration has never had a Senate-confirmed ICE Director.\n|-\n| [[File:Brock Long.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Brock Long]]\n| [[File:FEMA logo.svg|150px]]<br>[[Federal Emergency Management Agency|Administrator of the<br>Federal Emergency Management Agency]]\n| June 23, 2017\n| March 8, 2019\n| Announced his resignation February 13, effective March 8, 2019, with his deputy, [[Pete Gaynor]], to serve as acting administrator.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-13/fema-chief-brock-long-said-to-be-planning-to-leave-agency|title=FEMA Chief Brock Long Leaving Agency He Led Through Deadly Storms|publisher=Bloomberg|date=February 13, 2019|first1=Jennifer|last1=Jacobs|first2=Christopher|last2=Flavelle|access-date=February 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214034709/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-13/fema-chief-brock-long-said