issna-citizenship-and-immigration-services/index.html|title=Trump's Citizenship and Immigration Services director out|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=May 24, 2019|access-date=May 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524221505/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/05/24/politics/l-francis-cissna-citizenship-and-immigration-services/index.html|archive-date=May 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Ken Cuccinelli official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Ken Cuccinelli]]\n| style=\"background:gold\" | June 10, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\" | November 13, 2019\n| Became Acting Deputy Secretary of Homeland Security. In March 2020, Judge [[Randolph Moss]] ruled that his appointment as Acting USCIS Director violated the [[Federal Vacancies Reform Act of 1998]].\n|-\n| [[File:John_Kelly_Portrait_Deputy_IG2.png|100px]]<br>John V. Kelly\n| [[File:Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_Homeland_Security.svg|70x70px]]<br>[[Department of Homeland Security Office of Inspector General|DHS Inspector General]]\n| style=\"background:gold\" | December 1, 2017\n| style=\"background:gold\" | June 2019\n| Retired earlier than planned following revelations that he directed his staff to whitewash audits of DHS performance after federal disasters.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/homeland-security-watchdog-retires-early-after-his-office-was-forced-to-retract-feel-good-audits-of-disaster-response/2019/06/10/a370f488-8b9d-11e9-b08e-cfd89bd36d4e_story.html|title=Homeland Security watchdog retires early after his office was forced to retract 'feel-good' audits of disaster response|first1=Lisa|last1=Rein|first2=Kimberly|last2=Kindy|newspaper=Washington Post|date=June 10, 2019|access-date=June 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610200955/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/homeland-security-watchdog-retires-early-after-his-office-was-forced-to-retract-feel-good-audits-of-disaster-response/2019/06/10/a370f488-8b9d-11e9-b08e-cfd89bd36d4e_story.ht