hics rules should be tighter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/07/06/535781749/ethics-office-director-walter-shaub-resigns-saying-rules-need-to-be-tougher|title=Ethics Office Director Walter Shaub Resigns, Saying Rules Need To Be Tougher|accessdate=May 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180508103126/https://www.npr.org/2017/07/06/535781749/ethics-office-director-walter-shaub-resigns-saying-rules-need-to-be-tougher|archive-date=May 8, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=US government ethics chief resigns after clashes with Trump administration|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/07/06/us-government-ethics-chief-resigns-clashes-trump-administration/|website=United States Office of Government Ethics|publisher=The Telegraph|date=July 6, 2017|accessdate=March 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403232121/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/07/06/us-government-ethics-chief-resigns-clashes-trump-administration/|archive-date=April 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Jeff T. H. Pon official photo (cropped).jpg|100px]]<br>[[Jeff Tien Han Pon]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[File:Seal of the United States Office of Personnel Management.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[United States Office of Personnel Management|Director of the Office of Personnel Management]]\n| March 9, 2018\n| October 5, 2018\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Margaret Weichert official photo.png|100px]]<br>[[Margaret Weichert]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"| October 5, 2018\n| style=\"background:gold\"| September 16, 2019\n| The Senate confirmed Dale Cabaniss as OPM Director. Weichart remains the Deputy Director for Management in the Office of Management and Budget.\n|-\n| [[Dale Cabaniss]]\n| September 16, 2019\n| March 17, 2020\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=OPM chief Dale Cabaniss abruptly resigns|date=March 17, 2020|accessdate=March 17, 2020|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/17/dale-cabaniss-high-school-white-house-134541}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Ray Washburne official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Ray Washburne]]\n| [[File:OPIC logo2014 cmyk.png|75x75px]]<br>[[Overseas Private Investment Corporation|President and CEO of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation]]\n| September 5, 2017 \n| March 1, 2019\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Mel Watt official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Mel Watt]]\n| [[File:Seal of the United States Federal Housing Finance Agency.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[Federal Housing Finance Agency|Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency]]\n| January 6, 2014 \n| January 6, 2019\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Joseph Loddo, Administrator of the Small Business Administration of the United States Acting.png|100px]]<br>Joseph Loddo\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[File:US-SmallBusinessAdmin-Seal.svg|75x75px]]<br>[[Administrator of the Small Business Administration]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"| January 20, 2017\n| style=\"background:gold\"| February 14, 2017\n| \n|-\n| [[File:Linda McMahon official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Linda McMahon]]\n| February 14, 2017\n| April 12, 2019\n| In March 2019, the former [[WWE]] executive announced she was leaving the SBA to work for the America First Action SuperPAC.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/03/29/708088994/linda-mcmahon-to-quit-small-business-administration-joins-pro-trump-superpac|title=Linda McMahon To Quit Small Business Administration, Join Pro-Trump SuperPAC|date=March 29, 2019|first=Scott|last=Horsley|publisher=NPR|access-date=April 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401174338/https://www.npr.org/2019/03/29/708088994/linda-mcmahon-to-quit-small-business-administration-joins-pro-trump-superpac|archive-date=April 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Chris Pilkerton official photo (cropped).jpg|100px]]<br>[[Chris Pilkerton]]\n| style=\"background:gold\"| April 13, 2019\n| style=\"background:gold\"| January 13, 2020\n| Pilkerton remains the General Counsel of the SBA.\n|-\n| [[File:Althea Coetzee official photo.jpg|100px]]<br>[[Althea Coetzee]]\n|[[File:US-SmallBusinessAdmin-Seal.svg|75x75px]]